Program Purpose:
---------------

    This program implements file compression and decompression using
    Huffman coding. The encoder reads an ASCII text file, computes
    character frequencies, builds a Huffman tree, and writes a compressed
    binary file (.zap). The decoder reads a .zap file, reconstructs the
    Huffman tree, and restores the original text file exactly.

    The program supports two commands:
        - zap:   compress a text file into a .zap file
        - unzap: decompress a .zap file back into text

